			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2>105. <span style="color: #ff0000;">The Gift and Power: Translating the Book of Mormon</span></h2>
<h3><span style="color: #0000ff;">Author: Brandt Gardner</span></h3>
<p>The author, callers and I discussed some of the numerous topics related to the production of the Book of Mormon. These are several of the topics:</p>
<ul>
<li>Regarding to the Book of Mormon, what does translation mean?</li>
<li>Who gave the information - God, Angel, Joseph Smith or someone thought it up?</li>
<li>Who supplied the wording?</li>
<li>What are the believers views, or the non-believers?</li>
<li>What are the many varied views?</li>
</ul>
<h3><span style="color: #ff0000;">Talk Show host: Van Hale, LDS</span></h3>
<p><span style="color: #0000ff;"><em>Podcast address:</em></span> http://mormonmisc.podbean.com/
<em><span style="color: #0000ff;">Mormon Miscellaneous Worldwide Talk Show</span></em> now in its 32th year.
<span style="color: #ff0000;">TO PARTICIPATE:</span> Sunday evenings 5:00 - 7:00 pm MST
•    To listen to Talk Shows live, go to http://www.k-talk.com/
•    live by phone: 801-254-5855
•    or by email, write to: van.hale@yahoo.com
•    If you have a question or comment, your participation is invited, regardless of your point of view.</p>
