			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><span style="color: #0000ff;">104. <em>Development of Mormon Theology</em>.</span></h2>
<p><span style="color: #0000ff;">Date 2011-11-13</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #0000ff;">My guest, Charles Harrell, is the author of <em>This is My Doctrine: The Development of Mormon Theology</em>.</span><span style="color: #0000ff;"> </span></p>
<p>I highly recommend this book.</p>
<p>Some of the following are topics we discussed during our 2 hour discussion:</p>
<ul>
<li>Beliefs, doctrine &amp; opinions</li>
<li>The idea of official LDS doctrineMormon creeds?</li>
<li>Official position on passages of scripture</li>
<li>Revelation: past, present &amp; future</li>
<li>Considering past and present pronouncements</li>
<li>History of doctrinal changes</li>
<li>Dogmatism</li>
<li>De-emphasis</li>
</ul>
<h3><span style="color: #ff0000;">Talk Show host: Van Hale, LDS</span></h3>
<p>Podcast address: http://mormonmisc.podbean.com/</p>
<p>Mormon Miscellaneous Worldwide Talk Show is now in its 32th year. <strong></strong></p>
