			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h3><span style="color: #0000ff;">103.&#8221;Fires of Faith&#8221; The Translation
of the Bible into English</span></h3>
<p>2011-11-06</p>
<p>This year is the 400th anniversary of the King James Bible published in 1611.</p>
<p>BYUtv has produced an impressive 3 mini series which portrays and discusses the translations of the Bible in English from William Tyndale&#8217;s (1525) to the King James Version (1611).</p>
<p>My guest is Lee Groberg, an independent film producer. He is the director and producer for BYUtv&#8217;s remarkable documentary. He wrote, interviewed and coordinated filming with more than 400 actors and extras, eighteen international scholars, in eight different countries.</p>
<p>And with him are: Derek Marquis, the managing director of BYU Broadcasting and Fred Woods, Professor of Church History &amp; Doctrine and on the Hebrew from BYU.</p>
<h3><span style="color: #ff0000;">Talk Show host: Van Hale, LDS</span></h3>
<p>Podcast address: http://mormonmisc.podbean.com/</p>
<p>Mormon Miscellaneous Worldwide Talk Show now in its 32th year. <strong></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">TO PARTICIPATE:</span></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Sunday evenings 5:00 - 7:00 pm MST</li>
<li>To listen to Talk Shows live, go to http://www.k-talk.com</li>
