			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h3><span style="color: #0000ff;">94. Tales, Dubious Accuracy &amp; Testimony</span></h3>
<div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: x-small;">In this discussion I read early newspapers which frequently published articles which have turned out to be tales or dubious accuracy about Joseph Smith and the Mormons.</span></span></div>
<p><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: x-small;">Further, Martin Tanner discussed the difficulty determining conflicting testimonies so often found in our national court systems. Also, this creates problems when historians attempt to sort out many historical points.</span></span></p>
<p>8 December 2005 is the date of the program.</p>
<p>Van Hale was the host. Martin Tanner visited for the first hour.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>
</p>
]]></content:encoded>
