		<itunes:summary>94. Tales, Dubious Accuracy &#x38; Testimony
In this discussion I read early newspapers which frequently published articles which have turned out to be tales or dubious accuracy about Joseph Smith and the Mormons.
Further, Martin Tanner discussed the difficulty determining conflicting testimonies so often found in our national court systems. Also, this creates problems when historians attempt to sort out many historical points.

8 December 2005 is the date of the program.

Van Hale was the host. Martin Tanner visited for the first hour.

 
